sections.content:
When Jesus died, there was a great earthquake. The temple curtain was torn in two. (This symbolized that the Mosaic Age was over. The Christian Age was about to begin!) The first part of God's redemption plan had been accomplished. Jesus' death as the innocent and perfect sacrifice redeemed man from sin. Consider this:

• We all have sinned;
• God is holy and can have no part of sin;
• The ultimate fate for sinners is spiritual death in Hell;
• God has always used the pattern of innocent sacrifice redeeming the guilt of others; Jesus was innocent and without sin;
• We can be reconciled to God through Jesus' death.
